Barack Obama is also using Google-owned YouTube for addressing people. Google CEO Eric Schmidt previously endorsed Obama and is part of a  ...</description><category>Technology</category><category>Internet</category><category>Google</category><category>Search</category><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://blogoscoped.com/files/change-gov-google-moderator-large.png"><img src="http://blogoscoped.com/files/change-gov-google-moderator.png" alt="" /></a></p>

<p>Change.gov, website for US president-to-be Barack Obama&#8217;s transition team, has added a way <a href="http://change.gov/page/content/openforquestions">to ask questions</a> and vote on questions... using the <a href="http://moderator.appspot.com/">Google Moderator tool</a> released to the public <a href="http://blogoscoped.com/archive/2008-09-25-n65.html">earlier this year</a> (change.gov frame-embeds a page at <a href="http://moderator.change.gov/?embed=http://change.gov/openforquestions#15/e=8&amp;t=cf">moderator.change.gov</a>).</p>

<p>Barack Obama is also using Google-owned YouTube for <a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iGpIT2bVZDw">addressing people</a>. Google CEO Eric Schmidt previously endorsed Obama and is part of a 17-members team of economic advisers, as <a href="http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/000200811071774.htm">Hindu.com</a> reported last month.</p>

<p>On a related note, Change.gov recently switched <a href="http://change.gov/about/copyright_policy">from default copyright to Creative Commons</a>.</p>

