[Via Reddit. Image from the site.]</description><category>Technology</category><category>Internet</category><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://blogoscoped.com/files/evolved-image-2008-12.png" alt="" /></p>

<p>There&#8217;s now a <a href="http://alteredqualia.com/visualization/evolve/">configurable web app</a> for the semi-transparent vectors evolution <a href="http://rogeralsing.com/2008/12/07/genetic-programming-evolution-of-mona-lisa/">approach</a> mentioned earlier. Using Firefox <span style="font-size: 85%">(among other browsers, but not Internet Explorer &#8211; the page is Canvas-based)</span>, you provide a JPEG URL and then hit the Start button to watch the image mutate and evolve.</p>

